bidi-bidi
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[alteration of piripiri] a burred weed of the Acaena spp. that flaws fleecewool and that was used by colonists to augment tea leaves.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: also biddy-bid
Pronunciation:
